<!-- 
Trim Face Dialog UI - Qt Designer XML Layout

This UI file demonstrates conditional rendering for Phase 1 of Automatic Curve Extension.
Key UI patterns for novices to understand:

1. Conditional Visibility: extensionGroup is hidden by default (visible=false)
   - Shown/hidden programmatically based on curve coverage detection
   - Like React's {condition && <Component />} but with setVisible()

2. Event-Ready Structure: All interactive elements have object names
   - These names are referenced in dialog_panel.py for event handling
   - Example: extensionNoneRadio connects to on_extension_changed()

3. Progressive Disclosure: Advanced options appear when needed
   - Extension controls only show when curves are detected as short
   - Keeps interface clean for common use cases

4. Layout Hierarchy: Proper grouping with QGroupBox containers
   - Organizes related controls visually and logically
   - Makes the interface easier to understand and navigate
-->
